comment: Caldwell-Pope (DET) is in a legal guarding position and does not affect Knight's RSBQ on the perimeter.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes incidental contact with Knight (PHX) that does not affect his RSBQ at the start of the drive.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Ilyasova (DET) was attempting a 2 point field goal when he was fouled was overturned and Ilyasova was awarded three free throw attempts.
Teletovic (PHX) makes contact with Ilyasova's (DET) body that affects his jump shot attempt.
After securing the rebound, Knight (DET) gains no advantage by sliding and a timeout is called. A player who falls and slides with the ball only travels if he gains an advantage.
Jackson (DET) sets the screen on Knight (PHX) and does not give him room to avoid the contact as he continues moving into him.
Tucker (PHX) makes body to body contact with Drummond (DET) that affects his ability to set a screen.
Correctly called OOB last touched by Detroit. Phoenix retains possession.
Correctly called OOB last touched by Detroit. Phoenix retains possession.
Teletovic (PHX) and Ilyasova (DET) make incidental contact with one another during the inbounds play.
Tucker (PHX) sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ilyasova (DET) extends his leg unnaturally during a jump shot attempt and makes contact with Bledsoe (PHX), who legally contests the shot attempt.
LHH shows that Knight (PHX) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Jackson's (DET) driving layup attempt.
Ilyasova (DET) enters the paint area prior to the free throw being released.

Tucker (PHX) holds Jackson (DET) and affects his FOM away from the ball.
